### Stellar Expert REST API — Escrows by Participant
###
### Compatible with VS Code REST Client extension and HTTPie.
### Replace the variables below with real values before running.
###
### curl equivalents are shown in comments above each request.
###
### Reference: https://stellar.expert/openapi.html#tag/Contract-Events

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Variables — update these before running
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@network     = testnet
@base        = https://api.stellar.expert/explorer/{{network}}
@contract_id = CESCROW1111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111
@participant  = GSELLER111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111
@page_size   = 100

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1. Escrows where participant is SELLER
###    topic[0] = Symbol("Escrow"),  topic[1] = Symbol("Created"),
###    topic[2] = seller address
###
### curl:
###   curl -s "https://api.stellar.expert/explorer/testnet/contract-events
###     ?contract=$CONTRACT_ID
###     &topic0=0000000f00000006457363726f77
###     &topic1=0000000f000000074372656174656400
###     &topic2=$(stellar xdr encode --type ScVal --input json \
###               '{"type":"address","value":{"type":"account","account_id":"'$PARTICIPANT'"}}')
###     &order=asc&limit=100" | jq '.
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/contract-events
  ?contract={{contract_id}}
  &topic0=0000000f00000006457363726f77
  &topic1=0000000f000000074372656174656400
  &topic2={{participant_xdr}}
  &order=asc
  &limit={{page_size}}
Accept: application/json

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 2. Escrows where participant is BUYER
###    topic[0] = Symbol("Escrow"),  topic[1] = Symbol("Funded"),
###    topic[2] = buyer address
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/contract-events
  ?contract={{contract_id}}
  &topic0=0000000f00000006457363726f77
  &topic1=0000000f00000006 46756e646564
  &topic2={{participant_xdr}}
  &order=asc
  &limit={{page_size}}
Accept: application/json

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 3. Escrows where participant is RESOLVER (Dispute:Resolved)
###    topic[0] = Symbol("Dispute"),  topic[1] = Symbol("Resolved"),
###    topic[2] = resolver address
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/contract-events
  ?contract={{contract_id}}
  &topic0=0000000f000000074469737075746500
  &topic1=0000000f000000085265736f6c766564
  &topic2={{participant_xdr}}
  &order=asc
  &limit={{page_size}}
Accept: application/json

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 4. All disputes raised BY participant (buyer in Dispute:Raised)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/contract-events
  ?contract={{contract_id}}
  &topic0=0000000f000000074469737075746500
  &topic1=0000000f000000065261697365640000
  &topic2={{participant_xdr}}
  &order=asc
  &limit={{page_size}}
Accept: application/json

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 5. All escrow lifecycle events for the contract (no participant filter)
###    Returns every event across all escrows.  Paginate using the cursor
###    from _links.next.href until _links.next is absent.
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/contract-events
  ?contract={{contract_id}}
  &topic0=0000000f00000006457363726f77
  &order=asc
  &limit={{page_size}}
Accept: application/json

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 6. Next page — replace {{cursor}} with paging_token from previous response
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/contract-events
  ?contract={{contract_id}}
  &topic0=0000000f00000006457363726f77
  &order=asc
  &limit={{page_size}}
  &cursor={{cursor}}
Accept: application/json

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 7. Decode response — Node.js snippet (run after fetching):
###
###   import { xdr, scValToNative } from '@stellar/stellar-sdk'
###
###   for (const record of response._embedded.records) {
###     const topics = record.topic.map(t =>
###       scValToNative(xdr.ScVal.fromXDR(t, 'hex'))
###     )
###     const payload = scValToNative(xdr.ScVal.fromXDR(record.value, 'hex'))
###
###     // Guard against schema changes (see docs/events.md)
###     if (payload.schema_version > SUPPORTED_SCHEMA_VERSION) {
###       throw new Error(`Unsupported schema_version ${payload.schema_version}`)
###     }
###
###     console.log({
###       event_type:  `${topics[0]}:${topics[1]}`,
###       participant: topics[2],   // seller / buyer / resolver
###       escrow_id:   payload.escrow_id,
###       state:       payload.new_state,
###     })
###   }
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### HELPER: generate participant XDR hex with the Stellar CLI
###
###   stellar xdr encode --type ScVal --input json \
###     '{"type":"address","value":{"type":"account","account_id":"G..."}}'
###
### Pipe through xxd or hexdump to get the hex string for topic2= above:
###   stellar xdr encode --type ScVal --input json '...' | base64 -d | xxd -p -c 1000
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
